org.tensorics.core.tensor

Interface TensorView<V>

  • Type Parameters:
    V - the type of the values of the tensor
    All Superinterfaces:
    Tensor<V>

    public interface TensorView<V>
extends Tensor<V>
    Marks a tensor, which is a view on one or more other tensor(s). The main purpose of this interface is currently to make the fact of 'viewing' more explicit and let the user reflect on the consequences. (I.g. A tensor is not equal to its own view.)
